.TH grex-serve 1  "grex-serve " 
.SH NAME
grex\-serve \- Start MCP stdio server
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgrex\-serve\fR [\fB\-\-manifest\fR] [\fB\-\-workspace\fR] [\fB\-\-parallel\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Start MCP stdio server
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-manifest\fR=\fIPATH\fR
Path to the `grex.jsonl` event\-log manifest. Captured at server launch and immutable for the session (per spec §"Manifest binding"). Defaults to `<cwd>/grex.jsonl` when omitted
.TP
\fB\-\-workspace\fR=\fIPATH\fR
Workspace root the MCP server resolves relative paths against. Defaults to the current working directory when omitted
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR=\fIPARALLEL\fR
Harness\-level worker cap inherited by the MCP server\*(Aqs `Scheduler` (feat\-m7\-1 stage 8.3). `1` = serial; range `1..=1024`. Defaults to `std::thread::available_parallelism()` when omitted. Distinct from `sync \-\-parallel` which uses `0` = unbounded
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
